<TITLE> Hasina bail issue won't affect polls: adviser </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chittagong, Sept 30 (bdnews24.com)  Awami League chief Sheikh Hasina's failure to secure permanent bail will have no impact on the general elections, the commerce adviser said Tuesday. "The matter of allowing bail is the concern of the court. But it will not have any impact on the elections," said adviser Hossain Zillur Rahman. He spoke to reporters after a review meeting held at Chittagong Circuit House on the progress of the programmes taken for the development of the port city. "The government is ready to hold national elections in line with the roadmap. We hope the political parties will join the elections after preparations." "There is no scope for confusion about elections. The election ground is fully prepared. The political parties should take the opportunity to move the nation forward." Hossain Zillur termed the five-point charter of demands announced by the BNP-led four-party alliance as unfortunate. The adviser said the water refinery project of Chittagong WASA at Hathazari was at the final stages. "If it becomes operational water crisis in the city will go," he said. Among others acting Chittagong city corporation mayor M Monzur Alam, Chittagong divisional commissioner Hossain Jamil and deputy commissioner Ashraf Shamim were presen
